div.h1: Pre-LN vs Post-LN: Gradient Flow Comparison
div.h2: Why Pre-LayerNorm Enables Training Deep Transformers

div.p: In Post-LN, the residual connection is inside the LayerNorm:
Gradient must pass through LayerNorm's scaling.
In Pre-LN, the residual connection is outside:
Gradient flows through identity path stable training.
Problem: Gradient MUST flow through LayerNorm
Advantage: Gradient has CLEAN residual path
x' = x + Attention(LN(x)) out = x' (no final LN on output)
